caption: Best restaurant in Derry!!!

I got a lot of sushi for a great price! They'll give you a huge boat of sushi with a large variety for only $50. Everything is made fresh to order. My only complaint is that when I was there with my Mom, she left her purse and by the time we got to Manchester we realized what had happened. I called to let them know about her purse and they said they would take care of it. They ended up leaving her purse on the same chair that she sat in by the bar with other people seated around it without bringing it up to the front desk for safe keeping.

Great Sushi, Okay Tepanyaki. It is great to find a place in NH that has good sushi, there are so many mediocre to really bad places around. We tried the tepan/hibachi food and it was good, but not great. The fact that they charge the same prices for lower quality food without the usual show cooking at the table means we will be going to Masa in Manchester or Ichiban in Concord for hibachi in future....but for sushi, we will definitely be back to Sumo.
It gets crowded on weekends but the food is always good.  Rolls are huge and the restaurant has lots of different seating.
One of my favorite restaurants in Derry. Awesome hibachi, great sushi, and fantastic fast service
Fantastic food

Good quality of sushi and Japanese cuisine. Pretty standard affair for their offerings, but for area it's a breath of fresh air from the numerous local Americanized Chinese restaurants and Pizza joints. Location itself is easy to park at and eating in (if not during a pandemic) is enjoyable with a good mixture of traditional dining and space at the bar. Occasionally hiccups may occur during online ordering as their online purchasing system is a bit on the clumsy side. Overall, a good place to get Japanese food if you're in the area.
Really good sushi, big portions, good selection, fast service, highly recommended!

Exceptional and delightful food, I liked the character the place has, and the staff members were friendly. I will definitely eat here again.

Sushi is good. Service has gone drastically down hill. I specifically asked for extra soy sauce with my takeout order. Not only did they not give me soy sauce, they forgot chopsticks. This is not an uncommon occurrence. For an expensive restaurant I would expect much better. I will not be going back.

Soup and tempura were good, the rest (rice, salmon, maki, and the pad Thai) tasted so-so.  Maybe I'll try again for dine-in.

They are always willing to explain dishes to us if we aren't sure what is in them or what a particular sushi roll is comprised of.  The prices are reasonable and they also have happy hour.  We have been here many times and never left disappointed.  The menu is varied with a selection of traditional Chinese, sushi, hibachi, and some other items. Without a doubt my favorite local sushi spot. The prices and menu items are varied enough where you can either go for a casual date night dinner or something more celebratory. I've tried many items, including the hibachi, teriyaki, soup, fried rice, and sushi, and nothing has ever disappointed me. The fish is always fresh and your rolls are always made to order with a really beautiful presentation. There's a great variety of sushi as well. My personal favorite menu items are the fried shumai, the Tricolor Roll, the Orange Roll, and the Fantasy Roll. There's also lots of vegetarian friendly options, such as the tofu teriyaki and the veggie tempura dinner. Easily my favorite restaurant whether I'm going out with friends or just picking up a quick dinner.

Not bad, not exclusively sushi. Vegetarian options available for those so inclined. Was surprised to see Pad Thai as an option here - tried it - was okay. If you're looking for something different and like Japanese cuisine, give it a try.
